message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Colombia in the past 20 years is the signing of the peace agreement between the Colombian government and the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC) in 2016. After more than five decades of armed conflict, this agreement aimed to end the violence and establish a pathway to peace, reconciliation, and development. It involved various components such as the disarmament and demobilization of the FARC combatants, their reintegration into society, measures for truth, justice, and reparations for victims, and rural development initiatives. The peace agreement was a significant milestone in Colombia's history, representing a step towards ending the longest-running armed conflict in the Western Hemisphere and fostering a more peaceful and stable country.
